    "name": "Live Jimi Presley",
    "profile": "The band originated in Grahamstown in the mid to late 1980’s as the protest band Vader Jakob, before evolving into the Johannesburg-based Manhole in the early 1990’s. They reinvented themselves as Live Jimi Presley from 1992 -1997. The paradigm shifts in their music directly correlated with the mercurial shifts in politics at the time.\r\n\r\nLive Jimi Presley was essentially a socio-political performance band. The bands’ self-taught cross-genre sound combined elements of punk and industrial, with a local context of anger and vocal opposition against the system.\r\n\r\nTheir stage performance had been honed over several years from being quite ordinary to being a theatrical spectacle, ‘We practised six days a week and eventually got so good at performing the songs that we opted to focus on the theatrical performance. We’d add more props, costumes, masks and more grandeur every time we played certain songs’ remarks Tilo von Brandis (keyboards).\r\n\r\nPerformances were of such a nature that indemnit",
